-- MPE to Buy Shuttered Brazilian Sugar-Cane Mill, Valor Reports
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-07-02T13:45:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-02/mpe-to-buy-shuttered-brazilian-sugar-cane-mill-valor-reports.html
Montagens & Projetos Especiais SA, a
Brazilian engineering company, has agreed to buy a closed sugar
and ethanol mill in the state of Rio de Janeiro, according to
 Valor Economico .  MPE, as the company is known, will spend 70 million reais
($31.2 million) modernizing equipment and planting crops at
Usina Sapucaia SA’s sugar-cane mill in Campos dos Goytacazes,
the Sao Paulo-based newspaper  reported  today, citing MPE
President Renato Abreu.  Usina Sapucaia filed for bankruptcy in 2010 and hasn’t been
processing crops during the past few harvests, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in  Sao Paulo  at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
